'''José Manuel Lara Bosch''' (8 March 1946 &ndash; 31 January 2015) was a [[Spanish people|Spanish]] media executive and businessman. He was the [[CEO]] of [[Grupo Planeta]] since 2003 and [[Atresmedia]] since 2012. Bosch was born in [[Barcelona]], Spain.

Bosch died in Barcelona, Spain from [[pancreatic cancer]], aged 68.<ref>[http://ccaa.elpais.com/ccaa/2014/07/11/catalunya/1405105837_636595.html Fallece José Manuel Lara Bosch, el editor que llevó Planeta al futuro.] ''[[El País]]''. Date: 31 January 2015. {{es}}</ref> He is survived by his wife of 40 years, Consuelo García Píriz and his four children. 

