{{Infobox football biography | name= Martin van Geel | fullname = Martin van Geel | image = Martin van Geel.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|11|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Goirle]], [[Netherlands]] | height = | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[VOAB Goirle]] | years1 = 1977–1979 | years2 = 1979–1981 | years3 = 1981–1988 | years4 = 1988–1990 | years5 = 1990–1995 | clubs1 = [[Willem II Tilburg]] | clubs2 = [[Ajax Amsterdam]] | clubs3 = [[Roda JC]] | clubs4 = [[Feyenoord Rotterdam]] | clubs5 = [[Willem II Tilburg]] | caps1 = 33 | caps2 = 22 | caps3 = 196 | caps4 = 50 | caps5 = 133 | goals1 = 3 | goals2 = 9 | goals3 = 53 | goals4 = 24 | goals5 = 41 | manageryears1 = 1995–2002 | manageryears2 = 2002–2005 | manageryears3 = 2005–2007 | manageryears4 = 2008–2011 | manageryears5 = 2011– | managerclubs1 = [[Willem II Tilburg]] (technical director) | managerclubs2 = [[AZ Alkmaar]] (technical director) | managerclubs3 = [[Ajax Amsterdam]] (technical director) | managerclubs4 = [[Roda JC]] (technical director) | managerclubs5 = [[Feyenoord Rotterdam]] (technical director) | pcupdate = 8 June 2007 | ntupdate = 8 June 2007 }}
'''Martin van Geel''' (born 27 November 1960 in [[Goirle]]) is a retired [[Netherlands|Dutch]] footballer who was active as a midfielder. Van Geel made his professional debut on at 24 August 1977 [[Willem II Tilburg]], and also played for [[Ajax Amsterdam]], [[Roda JC]] and [[Feyenoord Rotterdam]].
